# Warehouse Coordination Framework

## Overview

Warehouse coordination ensures that order management, inventory planning, and logistics teams work effectively with fulfillment centers to execute wholesale orders.

Strong coordination allows warehouses to process orders efficiently while maintaining accuracy and compliance with retailer requirements.

---

## Purpose

Warehouse coordination helps operations teams:

• align order processing with warehouse capacity  
• ensure accurate inventory allocation  
• communicate shipment priorities  
• manage fulfillment schedules  

Effective coordination prevents operational bottlenecks.

---

## Core Coordination Activities

Operations teams typically coordinate with warehouse teams on:

• order release timing  
• inventory availability  
• shipment prioritization  
• fulfillment capacity planning  
• packaging and labeling requirements  

Clear communication ensures warehouses receive accurate instructions.

---

## Inventory Visibility

Warehouse coordination depends on accurate inventory data.

Operations teams must confirm:

• available inventory levels  
• reserved inventory for pending orders  
• replenishment schedules  
• inventory discrepancies

Accurate inventory visibility reduces fulfillment delays.

---

## Exception Handling

Warehouse coordination may require resolving issues such as:

• inventory shortages  
• incorrect product picking  
• damaged inventory  
• fulfillment delays  

Operations teams work with warehouse supervisors to resolve these issues quickly.

---

## Operational Communication

Common communication methods between operations and warehouses include:

• ERP order release notifications  
• warehouse management system updates  
• shipment schedules  
• exception alerts

Structured communication improves operational responsiveness.

---

## Final Note

Warehouse coordination ensures that digital order records translate into accurate physical shipments. Strong alignment between operations teams and fulfillment centers supports reliable order execution and customer satisfaction.
